{"repo": "hiyouga/EasyR1", "pull_number": 375, "instance_id": "hiyouga__EasyR1-375", "issue_numbers": [374], "base_commit": "51001bd457f4fbab0055b6a07341c4ac468b61e6", "patch": "diff --git a/examples/qwen3_14b_dapo17k_dapo.sh b/examples/qwen3_14b_dapo17k_dapo.sh\nindex 9d1908bf..402df602 100644\n--- a/examples/qwen3_14b_dapo17k_dapo.sh\n+++ b/examples/qwen3_14b_dapo17k_dapo.sh\n@@ -15,6 +15,8 @@ python3 -m verl.trainer.main \\\n     data.max_response_length=20480 \\\n     data.rollout_batch_size=512 \\\n     data.mini_rollout_batch_size=1536 \\\n+    worker.actor.micro_batch_size_per_device_for_update=1 \\\n+    worker.actor.micro_batch_size_per_device_for_experience=8 \\\n     worker.actor.model.model_path=${MODEL_PATH} \\\n     worker.actor.fsdp.torch_dtype=bf16 \\\n     worker.actor.optim.strategy=adamw_bf16 \\\ndiff --git a/verl/utils/torch_functional.py b/verl/utils/torch_functional.py\nindex 8392e545..0bf926ea 100644\n--- a/verl/utils/torch_functional.py\n+++ b/verl/utils/torch_functional.py\n@@ -64,7 +64,7 @@ def log_probs_from_logits(logits: torch.Tensor, labels: torch.Tensor) -> torch.T\n     if FLAH_ATTN_CROSS_ENTROPY_LOSS_AVAILABLE:\n         output = log_probs_from_logits_flash_attn(logits, labels)\n     else:  # fall back to torch kernel, upcast logits to fp32\n-        output = F.cross_entropy(logits.float(), labels, reduction=\"none\")\n+        output = -F.cross_entropy(logits.float(), labels, reduction=\"none\")\n \n     return output.view(*batch_dim)\n \n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "log_prob \u7684\u8ba1\u7b97\u95ee\u9898\n\u5728 https://github.com/hiyouga/EasyR1/blob/51001bd457f4fbab0055b6a07341c4ac468b61e6/verl/utils/torch_functional.py#L67 \u4e2d\uff0c\u8ba1\u7b97 log_prob \u7684\u51fd\u6570\u4e3a\uff1a\n```\ndef log_probs_from_logits(logits: torch.Tensor, labels: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:\n    ...\n    if FLAH_ATTN_CROSS_ENTROPY_LOSS_AVAILABLE:\n        output = log_probs_from_logits_flash_attn(logits, labels)\n    else:  # fall back to torch kernel, upcast logits to fp32\n        output = F.cross_entropy(logits.float(), labels, reduction=\"none\")\n\n    return output.view(*batch_dim)\n```\n\n\u5f53 if \u89e6\u53d1\u7684\u65f6\u5019\uff0c\u8f93\u51fa\uff1a\n```\n@torch.compiler.disable()\ndef log_probs_from_logits_flash_attn(logits: torch.Tensor, labels: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:\n    output = cross_entropy_loss(logits, labels, inplace_backward=True)\n    if not isinstance(output, tuple):\n        raise ValueError(\n            \"please make sure flash-attn>=2.4.3 where cross_entropy_loss returns Tuple[losses, z_losses].\"\n        )\n\n    return -output[0]\n```\n\u5f53else\u89e6\u53d1\u5219\u8fd4\u56de\uff1a\n```\noutput = F.cross_entropy(logits.float(), labels, reduction=\"none\")\n\n    return output.view(*batch_dim)\n```\n\u8fd9\u91cc\u7684\u6b63\u8d1f\u53f7\u597d\u50cf\u6709\u4e00\u4e9b\u95ee\u9898\uff1fcross_entropy\u4e00\u822c\u5f97\u5230\u7684\u662f loss\uff0c\u5e94\u8be5\u662f\u8fd4\u56de\u975e\u8d1f\u6570\u7684\uff1f\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "else \u7684\u5206\u652f\u7684\u786e\u6709\u95ee\u9898\uff0c\u5df2\u7ecf\u4fee\u590d\u3002\u73b0\u5728 else \u7684\u4ee3\u7801\u51e0\u4e4e\u4e0d\u4f1a\u6267\u884c\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/hiyouga/EasyR1/commit/607609c8aa0d37ccff11e3045c1033aa8d1770f6"], "created_at": "2025-06-19T11:48:59Z"}
{"repo": "hiyouga/EasyR1", "pull_number": 387, "instance_id": "hiyouga__EasyR1-387", "issue_numbers": [379], "base_commit": "bd3b4eb275858421f12cac8d5d800ef353b0c8d0", "patch": "diff --git a/verl/trainer/config.py b/verl/trainer/config.py\nindex 94f25b0e..a11ffff6 100644\n--- a/verl/trainer/config.py\n+++ b/verl/trainer/config.py\n@@ -53,6 +53,7 @@ class DataConfig:\n     min_pixels: Optional[int] = 262144\n     max_pixels: Optional[int] = 4194304\n     filter_overlong_prompts: bool = True\n+    filter_overlong_prompts_workers: int = 16\n \n     def post_init(self):\n         if self.image_dir is not None:\ndiff --git a/verl/trainer/data_loader.py b/verl/trainer/data_loader.py\nindex aff12fb9..f5167691 100644\n--- a/verl/trainer/data_loader.py\n+++ b/verl/trainer/data_loader.py\n@@ -40,6 +40,7 @@ def create_dataloader(config: DataConfig, tokenizer: PreTrainedTokenizer, proces\n         min_pixels=config.min_pixels,\n         max_pixels=config.max_pixels,\n         filter_overlong_prompts=config.filter_overlong_prompts,\n+        filter_overlong_prompts_workers=config.filter_overlong_prompts_workers,\n     )\n     # use sampler for better ckpt resume\n     if config.shuffle:\ndiff --git a/verl/utils/dataset.py b/verl/utils/dataset.py\nindex 1130a6c4..211e09d8 100644\n--- a/verl/utils/dataset.py\n+++ b/verl/utils/dataset.py\n@@ -107,6 +107,7 @@ def __init__(\n         min_pixels: Optional[int] = None,\n         max_pixels: Optional[int] = None,\n         filter_overlong_prompts: bool = True,\n+        filter_overlong_prompts_workers: int = 16,\n     ):\n         self.tokenizer = tokenizer\n         self.processor = processor\n@@ -120,7 +121,6 @@ def __init__(\n         self.truncation = truncation\n         self.min_pixels = min_pixels\n         self.max_pixels = max_pixels\n-        self.filter_overlong_prompts = filter_overlong_prompts\n \n         if \"@\" in data_path:\n             data_path, data_split = data_path.split(\"@\")\n@@ -143,9 +143,11 @@ def __init__(\n             with open(format_prompt, encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n                 self.format_prompt = f.read()\n \n-        if self.filter_overlong_prompts:\n+        if filter_overlong_prompts:\n             self.dataset = self.dataset.filter(\n-                self._filter_overlong_prompts, desc=\"Filtering overlong prompts\", num_proc=16\n+                self._filter_overlong_prompts,\n+                desc=\"Filtering overlong prompts\",\n+                num_proc=filter_overlong_prompts_workers,\n             )\n \n     def _build_messages(self, example: Dict[str, Any]) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]:\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "\u600e\u4e48\u52a0\u901fFiltering overlong prompts\uff1f\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d39062f0-d8db-4468-93c6-96bc7b84b90b)\n\u5982\u56fe\uff0c\u6211\u8fdb\u884cFiltering overlong prompts\u8981\u8017\u8d391\u4e2a\u5c0f\u65f6\u4ee5\u4e0a\uff0c\u800c\u4e14easyr1\u597d\u50cf\u6ca1\u6709filter_overlong_prompts_workers\u7684\u8fd9\u4e2a\u53c2\u6570\uff0c\u90a3\u6211\u5982\u4f55\u52a0\u901f\u8fd9\u4e00\u8fdb\u7a0b\u5462\uff1f\n", "hints_text": "\u53ef\u4ee5\u5728 config.yaml \u91cc\u5173\u95ed\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\u53ef\u4ee5\u5728 config.yaml \u91cc\u5173\u95ed\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/hiyouga/EasyR1/commit/41ffa95fd6c215970dec6f8c6436c36968d78be7"], "created_at": "2025-06-23T12:29:45Z"}
{"repo": "hiyouga/EasyR1", "pull_number": 396, "instance_id": "hiyouga__EasyR1-396", "issue_numbers": [395], "base_commit": "c19396ea16edc383cb25fedb3da58ae08e08046e", "patch": "diff --git a/verl/workers/fsdp_workers.py b/verl/workers/fsdp_workers.py\nindex d6bc67c8..1dc2adbd 100644\n--- a/verl/workers/fsdp_workers.py\n+++ b/verl/workers/fsdp_workers.py\n@@ -474,7 +474,7 @@ def _process_multi_modal_inputs(self, data: DataProto):\n                     batch_multi_modal_inputs.append(multi_modal_inputs)\n                 elif len(videos) != 0:\n                     multi_modal_inputs = dict(\n-                        self.processor.image_processor(images=None, videos=video, return_tensors=\"pt\")\n+                        self.processor.image_processor(images=None, videos=videos, return_tensors=\"pt\")\n                     )\n                     multi_modal_inputs = {k: v.to(torch.cuda.current_device()) for k, v in multi_modal_inputs.items()}\n                     batch_multi_modal_inputs.append(multi_modal_inputs)\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Possible Typo in fsdp_workers.py:477 for Video Inputs\nHi @hiyouga ,\n\nhttps://github.com/hiyouga/EasyR1/blob/c19396ea16edc383cb25fedb3da58ae08e08046e/verl/workers/fsdp_workers.py#L477\n\nShould this line be updated to:\nself.processor.image_processor(images=None, videos=video**s**, return_tensors=\"pt\")?\n\nThanks!\n", "hints_text": "Sure, would you mind creating a PR to fix this?\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Sure, would you mind creating a PR to fix this?\n@hiyouga Sure! I have created the PR here (https://github.com/hiyouga/EasyR1/pull/396)\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/hiyouga/EasyR1/commit/7a450c8663bc3d19e00cd5576d93d4686e4e0a34"], "created_at": "2025-06-25T14:04:57Z"}
